FBIS3-54796 "drsov002_p_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-002 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Jan 1994 CAUCASUS Armenia New Food, Service Prices Fixed on 4 Jan NC0301213694 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network in Armenian 2000 GMT 3 Jan 94 NC0301213694 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network in Armenian 2000 GMT 3 Jan 94 Language: Armenian Article Type:BFN [Text] In order to expand commodity circulation in the consumer market and reduce production (?losses), the Armenian Government has decided to establish new retail prices for bread, flour, and basic services as of 4 January. The retail price of bread has been fixed at 1.50 dram, or 300 rubles, per kilo; flour at 1.21 dram, or 250 rubles, per kilo. The rate for electricity has been fixed at .20 dram, or 40 rubles per kilowatt-hour. Inter-city passenger transportation on buses, trolleys, and trams has been fixed at .50 dram, or 100 rubles, per person. The cost of basic services--such as rent, water, garbage collection, and telephone service--have also been increased by an average of two-and-a-half times more than their previous cost. Detailed information will be published in the press.
